==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Engorge
<hw>En*gorge"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Engorged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Engorging</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>en-</ets> + <ets>gorge</ets>: cf. F. <ets>engorger</ets> to
obstruct, cram.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To gorge; to glut.</def>
<rj><au>Mir. for Mag.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To swallow with greediness or in large quantities;
to devour.</def> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Engorge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Engorge
<hw>En*gorge"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To feed with eagerness or
voracity; to stuff one's self with food.</def>
<rj><au>Beaumont.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Engorged</ent>⟦br⟧
